1
00:00:01,583 --> 00:00:06,834
DATA:
<i>Second Officer's Personal Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 44390.1.</i>

2
00:00:06,875 --> 00:00:10,417
<i>Record entry for transmission</i>
<i>to Commander Bruce Maddox</i>

3
00:00:10,458 --> 00:00:13,291
<i>Cybernetics Division,</i>
<i>Daystrom Institute.</i>

4
00:00:13,333 --> 00:00:14,792
<i>Dear Commander Maddox</i>

5
00:00:14,834 --> 00:00:17,000
<i>in reference</i>
<i>to your most recent letter</i>

6
00:00:17,041 --> 00:00:20,417
<i>I agree that your study lacks</i>
<i>sufficient primary source</i>

7
00:00:20,458 --> 00:00:23,083
<i>information on my programming</i>
<i>and operation.</i>

8
00:00:23,125 --> 00:00:26,542
<i>Therefore, in response to your</i>
<i>request, this correspondence</i>

9
00:00:26,583 --> 00:00:28,041
<i>will include a complete record</i>

10
00:00:28,083 --> 00:00:30,083
<i>of my activities</i>
<i>during a normal day</i>

11
00:00:30,125 --> 00:00:33,458
<i>with particular emphasis on</i>
<i>my perceptions of friendship.</i>

12
00:00:36,041 --> 00:00:38,375
Commander Riker,
you are 15 minutes early.

13
00:00:38,417 --> 00:00:39,834
Well, it's a very special day.

14
00:00:39,875 --> 00:00:41,875
I thought the father
of the bride would enjoy

15
00:00:41,917 --> 00:00:43,667
being relieved early
on the wedding day.

16
00:00:43,709 --> 00:00:44,792
Thank you, sir.

17
00:00:44,834 --> 00:00:45,792
Nervous?

18
00:00:45,834 --> 00:00:47,417
I cannot become nervous, sir.

19
00:00:47,458 --> 00:00:50,041
However, I do sense
a certain... anticipation

20
00:00:50,083 --> 00:00:52,250
regarding my role
in the wedding.

21
00:00:52,291 --> 00:00:53,917
Anything to report?

22
00:00:53,959 --> 00:00:55,959
All systems are normal, sir.

23
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,375
Sick Bay reports
that Lieutenant Juarez
went into labor at 0400.

24
00:01:00,417 --> 00:01:03,250
We remain at station
awaiting the arrival
of Starship<i> Zhukov</i>

25
00:01:03,291 --> 00:01:05,375
and guest quarters
have been prepared
for Ambassador T'Pel.

26
00:01:05,417 --> 00:01:06,375
Thank you.

27
00:01:06,417 --> 00:01:07,417
I have the Bridge.

28
00:01:07,458 --> 00:01:08,750
Aye, sir.

29
00:01:09,792 --> 00:01:11,041
Begin day watch.

30
00:01:11,083 --> 00:01:13,000
DATA:
<i>Initially, Commander Maddox</i>

31
00:01:13,041 --> 00:01:15,458
<i>I found it difficult</i>
<i>to maintain friendships</i>

32
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:18,500
<i>since human emotions</i>
<i>are often puzzling to me.</i>

33
00:01:22,417 --> 00:01:24,834
<i>Eventually,</i>
<i>I developed a program</i>

34
00:01:24,875 --> 00:01:28,166
<i>enabling me to predict</i>
<i>human emotional responses</i>

35
00:01:28,208 --> 00:01:29,709
<i>to specific actions.</i>

36
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:31,291
(<i> door chimes</i> )

37
00:01:33,166 --> 00:01:34,709
Come in.

38
00:01:37,709 --> 00:01:39,917
It is time for the
wedding rehearsal.

39
00:01:39,959 --> 00:01:41,458
I know.

40
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:44,834
Data, I've decided
not to go through with it.

41
00:01:44,875 --> 00:01:46,959
You do not wish to rehearse?

42
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,792
No, I'm calling off the wedding.

43
00:01:49,834 --> 00:01:51,750
May I ask why?

44
00:01:51,792 --> 00:01:54,667
It's just the right thing to do.

45
00:01:54,709 --> 00:01:58,417
Have your feelings
for Chief O'Brien changed?

46
00:02:02,917 --> 00:02:05,667
I'm supposed
to be getting married, Data.

47
00:02:05,709 --> 00:02:07,333
I should be happy, but I'm not.

48
00:02:07,375 --> 00:02:08,667
I just feel this weight

49
00:02:08,709 --> 00:02:10,417
pressing down on me.

50
00:02:10,458 --> 00:02:13,291
Will canceling the wedding
make you happy?

51
00:02:14,375 --> 00:02:15,834
Yes.

52
00:02:15,875 --> 00:02:19,917
He'll probably
be just as relieved as I am.

53
00:02:19,959 --> 00:02:21,875
Data

54
00:02:21,917 --> 00:02:24,291
you introduced us to each other.

55
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:26,750
You mean a lot to both of us.

56
00:02:26,792 --> 00:02:28,875
I would really appreciate it

57
00:02:28,917 --> 00:02:31,750
if you would talk to Miles
for me.

58
00:02:31,792 --> 00:02:33,583
If you wish.

59
00:02:42,667 --> 00:02:44,834
<i>My friend Chief O'Brien</i>
<i>often says</i>

60
00:02:44,875 --> 00:02:47,834
<i>that above all else,</i>
<i>he wants to make Keiko happy.</i>

61
00:02:47,875 --> 00:02:50,125
<i>Since canceling the wedding</i>
<i>will make her happy</i>

62
00:02:50,166 --> 00:02:53,000
<i>I must conclude the Chief will</i>
<i>be pleased at her decision.</i>

63
00:02:53,041 --> 00:02:54,291
I have good news.

64
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:55,875
Oh?

65
00:02:55,917 --> 00:02:57,625
Keiko has made a decision

66
00:02:57,667 --> 00:03:00,166
designed to increase
her happiness.

67
00:03:00,208 --> 00:03:02,041
She has canceled the wedding.

68
00:03:02,083 --> 00:03:03,917
She what?

69
00:03:03,959 --> 00:03:06,500
Canceled the wedding?!

70
00:03:06,542 --> 00:03:08,166
Today?

71
00:03:08,208 --> 00:03:09,834
Without even a word?

72
00:03:09,875 --> 00:03:14,750
Of all the childish, selfish,
irresponsible things to do!

73
00:03:14,792 --> 00:03:18,917
Next time, maybe I should
deliver the good news.

74
00:03:20,583 --> 00:03:23,709
<i>Commander Maddox,</i>
<i>it would appear that my</i>
<i>program</i>

75
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:29,333
<i>designed to predict emotional</i>
<i>responses needs... adjustment.</i>

76
00:03:56,333 --> 00:04:00,750
<i>Space, the final frontier.</i>

77
00:04:00,792 --> 00:04:04,709
<i>These are the voyages</i>
<i>of the Starship</i> Enterprise.

78
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:06,583
<i>Its continuing mission--</i>

79
00:04:06,625 --> 00:04:10,542
<i>to explore</i>
<i>strange new worlds</i>

80
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:14,959
<i>to seek out new life</i>
<i>and new civilizations</i>

81
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:19,625
<i>to boldly go</i>
<i>where no one has gone before.</i>

82
00:05:16,917 --> 00:05:20,208
DATA:
<i>Second Officer's Personal Log,</i>
<i>supplemental.</i>

83
00:05:20,250 --> 00:05:22,041
<i>This is the 1,550th day</i>

84
00:05:22,083 --> 00:05:23,667
<i>since the</i> Enterprise
<i>was commissioned.</i>

85
00:05:23,709 --> 00:05:26,709
<i>Besides the arrival</i>
<i>of Ambassador T'Pel</i>

86
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:28,291
<i>other events occurring today</i>

87
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:30,625
<i>include four birthdays,</i>
<i>two personal transfers</i>

88
00:05:30,667 --> 00:05:33,583
<i>a celebration</i>
<i>of the Hindu Festival of</i>
<i>Lights</i>

89
00:05:33,625 --> 00:05:36,125
<i>two chess tournaments,</i>
<i>one secondary school play</i>

90
00:05:36,166 --> 00:05:37,542
<i>and four promotions.</i>

91
00:05:37,583 --> 00:05:39,834
<i>Overall, an ordinary day.</i>

92
00:05:39,875 --> 00:05:42,333
The<i> Zhukov</i> is ready
for transport, sir.

93
00:05:42,375 --> 00:05:44,417
Energize.

94
00:05:50,625 --> 00:05:53,917
Welcome aboard the<i> Enterprise,</i>
Ambassador.

95
00:05:53,959 --> 00:05:56,959
I would meet
with your Captain.

96
00:06:00,709 --> 00:06:03,583
<i>Since I am not affected</i>
<i>by emotional considerations</i>

97
00:06:03,625 --> 00:06:06,000
<i>I am closer to being Vulcan</i>
<i>than human.</i>

98
00:06:06,041 --> 00:06:07,792
<i>However, while their devotion</i>
<i>to logic</i>

99
00:06:07,834 --> 00:06:09,583
<i>does have a certain appeal</i>

100
00:06:09,625 --> 00:06:13,917
<i>I find their stark philosophy</i>
<i>to be somewhat... limited.</i>

101
00:06:13,959 --> 00:06:14,959
(<i> door chimes</i> )

102
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,250
Come.

103
00:06:17,291 --> 00:06:18,834
Ambassador T'Pel.

104
00:06:18,875 --> 00:06:20,208
I come to serve.

105
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:21,792
Your service honors us.

106
00:06:21,834 --> 00:06:24,333
This is my First Officer,
Commander William Riker.

107
00:06:24,375 --> 00:06:26,291
Leave us, please.

108
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:37,166
<i>Charming</i> woman.

109
00:06:37,208 --> 00:06:38,792
<i>The tone</i>
<i>of Commander Riker's voice</i>

110
00:06:38,834 --> 00:06:40,917
<i>makes me suspect</i>
<i>that he is not serious</i>

111
00:06:40,959 --> 00:06:43,333
<i>about finding</i>
<i>Ambassador T'Pel charming.</i>

112
00:06:43,375 --> 00:06:46,542
<i>My experience suggests</i>
<i>that, in fact, he may mean</i>

113
00:06:46,583 --> 00:06:48,917
<i>the exact opposite</i>
<i>of what he says.</i>

114
00:06:48,959 --> 00:06:50,458
<i>Irony is a form of expression</i>

115
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:52,917
<i>I have not yet</i>
<i>been able to master.</i>

116
00:06:52,959 --> 00:06:54,542
You don't need
a haircut.

117
00:06:54,583 --> 00:06:56,166
You were just
in here last week.

118
00:06:56,208 --> 00:06:58,083
Hey, if you'd done it
right the first time

119
00:06:58,125 --> 00:06:59,792
I wouldn't need to be
back here so soon.

120
00:06:59,834 --> 00:07:01,959
(<i> chuckles</i> ):
I know you want
to look beautiful

121
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:04,959
but I'm just a barber,
not a miracle worker.

122
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:08,000
Just try to keep my ears
on straight today, all right?

123
00:07:08,041 --> 00:07:10,000
<i>Friendly insults and jibes--</i>

124
00:07:10,041 --> 00:07:13,000
<i>another form of human speech</i>
<i>that I am attempting to</i>
<i>master.</i>

125
00:07:13,041 --> 00:07:16,250
<i>In this case, with the help</i>
<i>of Commander Geordi La Forge.</i>

126
00:07:16,291 --> 00:07:18,166
Hi, Data.

127
00:07:18,208 --> 00:07:21,834
<i>I consider Geordi</i>
<i>to be my best friend.</i>

128
00:07:21,875 --> 00:07:23,458
Here for a trim?

129
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:26,458
My hair does not require
trimming, you lunkhead.

130
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:28,041
What?

131
00:07:28,083 --> 00:07:29,500
My hair does not require
trimming...

132
00:07:29,542 --> 00:07:31,000
Lunkhead?

133
00:07:31,041 --> 00:07:33,792
I am experimenting
with friendly jibes and insults.

134
00:07:33,834 --> 00:07:36,083
It was not meant
as a serious disparagement.

135
00:07:36,125 --> 00:07:37,709
(<i> chuckles</i> )

136
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:40,583
Well... just don't try it
on the Captain.

137
00:07:40,625 --> 00:07:42,959
No.

138
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:46,166
Geordi, I am still confused

139
00:07:46,208 --> 00:07:48,583
by Chief O'Brien's reaction
this morning.

140
00:07:48,625 --> 00:07:50,125
Mm, yeah.

141
00:07:50,166 --> 00:07:51,709
He was just surprised, Data.

142
00:07:51,750 --> 00:07:53,875
He didn't mean
to blow up like that.

143
00:07:53,917 --> 00:07:55,375
He knows that Keiko

144
00:07:55,417 --> 00:07:57,667
probably doesn't want
to call off the marriage.

145
00:07:57,709 --> 00:07:59,583
She's just getting cold feet.

146
00:07:59,625 --> 00:08:01,000
(<i> instrument humming</i> )

147
00:08:01,041 --> 00:08:02,792
Cold feet?

148
00:08:02,834 --> 00:08:03,792
Jitters.

149
00:08:03,834 --> 00:08:05,041
A nervous reaction

150
00:08:05,083 --> 00:08:07,500
to an impending event
of great importance.

151
00:08:07,542 --> 00:08:09,542
Right.
Don't worry.

152
00:08:09,583 --> 00:08:11,208
Everything's
going to be fine.

153
00:08:11,250 --> 00:08:12,959
She'll change her mind again.

154
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,208
She will?

155
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:16,000
Absolutely.

156
00:08:16,041 --> 00:08:18,917
So, you believe that
the marriage will still proceed?

157
00:08:18,959 --> 00:08:20,625
Trust me.

158
00:08:20,667 --> 00:08:24,291
They're going to get married,
so you'd better find a gift.

159
00:08:25,875 --> 00:08:27,834
<i>I find Lieutenant Worf</i>

160
00:08:27,875 --> 00:08:30,083
<i>to be what is called</i>
<i>a kindred spirit.</i>

161
00:08:30,125 --> 00:08:33,208
<i>We were both orphans</i>
<i>rescued by Starfleet officers.</i>

162
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:38,542
<i>In many ways, we are both still</i>
<i>outsiders in human society.</i>

163
00:08:38,583 --> 00:08:42,166
Are you here
to find a wedding gift?
Yes.

164
00:08:42,208 --> 00:08:45,750
I would appreciate
your help in selecting
an appropriate item.

165
00:08:45,792 --> 00:08:47,375
Of course.

166
00:08:47,417 --> 00:08:50,834
I have attended human
weddings before.

167
00:08:53,667 --> 00:08:54,917
WORF:
Hold.

168
00:08:54,959 --> 00:08:56,667
DATA:
This is a
traditional gift?

169
00:08:56,709 --> 00:09:02,000
Yes, my adoptive parents
often give these...<i> things</i>

170
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:04,583
at family weddings.

171
00:09:04,625 --> 00:09:07,208
A human custom.

172
00:09:09,417 --> 00:09:11,041
WORF:
Hold.

173
00:09:11,083 --> 00:09:14,750
It is my understanding
that the item selected

174
00:09:14,792 --> 00:09:17,625
should reflect the personality
of whoever is giving it.

175
00:09:17,667 --> 00:09:19,959
This does not
remind me of you.

176
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:24,542
Have you ever been
an actual participant

177
00:09:24,583 --> 00:09:25,792
in a human wedding?

178
00:09:25,834 --> 00:09:27,625
No.

179
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:30,625
You would not consider it
to be an honor?

180
00:09:30,667 --> 00:09:32,667
An honor, perhaps

181
00:09:32,709 --> 00:09:34,875
but human
bonding rituals

182
00:09:34,917 --> 00:09:38,291
often involve a
great deal of talking

183
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:40,583
and dancing and...

184
00:09:40,625 --> 00:09:42,625
crying.

185
00:09:42,667 --> 00:09:44,583
Dancing?

186
00:09:47,875 --> 00:09:49,417
<i>I am rarely in need</i>

187
00:09:49,458 --> 00:09:51,959
<i>of Dr. Beverly Crusher's</i>
<i>professional services</i>

188
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,750
<i>as my biomechanical</i>
<i>maintenance program</i>

189
00:09:53,792 --> 00:09:55,500
<i>is self-sufficient</i>

190
00:09:55,542 --> 00:09:58,709
<i>but I often observe as she</i>
<i>practices medicine on others</i>

191
00:09:58,750 --> 00:10:00,041
<i>and have learned a great deal</i>

192
00:10:00,083 --> 00:10:03,291
<i>about human interaction</i>
<i>from her.</i>

193
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:06,208
Doctor, may I ask
a favor of you?

194
00:10:06,250 --> 00:10:07,375
Of course, Data.

195
00:10:07,417 --> 00:10:09,875
Would you teach
me to dance?

196
00:10:12,291 --> 00:10:13,583
What?!

197
00:10:13,625 --> 00:10:15,417
I would like to learn
how to dance.

198
00:10:15,458 --> 00:10:16,417
Why me?

199
00:10:16,458 --> 00:10:18,208
It was in your service record--

200
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:20,458
"Awarded first prize, tap and
jazz competition, St. Louis..."

201
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:23,375
Okay, okay.

202
00:10:23,417 --> 00:10:25,375
Have I said something
to upset you?

203
00:10:25,417 --> 00:10:29,417
It's just that... that
was a long time ago

204
00:10:29,458 --> 00:10:32,625
and I don't want to be known
as "The Dancing Doctor..."

205
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:34,333
again.

206
00:10:34,375 --> 00:10:36,792
Then your answer is no.

207
00:10:37,792 --> 00:10:40,166
All right, but...

208
00:10:40,208 --> 00:10:44,125
let's keep this
between you and me.

209
00:10:44,166 --> 00:10:45,959
Of course, Doctor.

210
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:49,250
PICARD:
Commander Data,
please report to the Bridge.

211
00:10:49,291 --> 00:10:50,709
Acknowledged.

212
00:10:53,834 --> 00:10:55,500
(<i> door opens</i> )

213
00:10:55,542 --> 00:10:58,083
Data, I want a tactical
projection of possible

214
00:10:58,125 --> 00:11:00,291
Romulan deployments
along the Neutral Zone.

215
00:11:00,333 --> 00:11:02,750
Access all Federation
records on the subject

216
00:11:02,792 --> 00:11:04,375
and report
to my ready room.

217
00:11:04,417 --> 00:11:07,709
Captain, is there a specific
area you wish me to study?

218
00:11:10,417 --> 00:11:13,208
No.
Ambassador.

219
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:18,125
Number One, set a course
130 mark 246, warp seven.

220
00:11:18,166 --> 00:11:20,458
That will take us very close
to the Neutral Zone, Captain.

221
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:23,625
I'm aware of
that, Number One.
Proceed.

222
00:11:23,667 --> 00:11:25,375
Lay in the course.

223
00:11:29,625 --> 00:11:33,041
<i>It is fortunate that I am</i>
<i>able to perform my duties</i>

224
00:11:33,083 --> 00:11:36,250
<i>without emotional distractions.</i>

225
00:11:36,291 --> 00:11:37,959
<i>If that were not the case</i>

226
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,375
<i>a sudden course correction</i>
<i>toward the Neutral Zone</i>

227
00:11:40,417 --> 00:11:44,750
<i>would make me very...</i>
<i>nervous.</i>

228
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:55,709
Mr. Data, based

229
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:56,875
on your analysis

230
00:11:56,917 --> 00:11:58,917
what is the current
Romulan strategy

231
00:11:58,959 --> 00:12:01,333
behind the deployment
of their ships in this sector?

232
00:12:01,375 --> 00:12:02,875
Their ships are deployed

233
00:12:02,917 --> 00:12:05,750
to support a policy of
confrontation designed to test

234
00:12:05,792 --> 00:12:08,041
Federation defenses
along the Neutral Zone.

235
00:12:08,083 --> 00:12:10,083
Do you predict any change
in the near future?

236
00:12:10,125 --> 00:12:12,208
I predict a 90% probability

237
00:12:12,250 --> 00:12:15,125
that they will continue
to support that policy.

238
00:12:15,166 --> 00:12:16,542
