00:25:04,625 --> 00:25:07,041
Now you'll notice that
I don't just repeat

500
00:25:07,083 --> 00:25:09,000
the same pattern over and over.

501
00:25:09,041 --> 00:25:10,792
I improvise.

502
00:25:12,333 --> 00:25:13,875
Now you lead.

503
00:25:17,750 --> 00:25:19,709
That's good.

504
00:25:19,750 --> 00:25:21,917
Now look up, Data.

505
00:25:21,959 --> 00:25:24,041
Look into my eyes.

506
00:25:24,083 --> 00:25:26,083
You're holding me too tight.

507
00:25:26,125 --> 00:25:29,083
This is a very complex
set of variables

508
00:25:29,125 --> 00:25:30,333
to coordinate, Doctor.

509
00:25:30,375 --> 00:25:32,083
You are doing fine.

510
00:25:32,125 --> 00:25:33,917
Now, smile.

511
00:25:33,959 --> 00:25:37,917
Act like you're
enjoying yourself.

512
00:25:37,959 --> 00:25:41,208
NURSE:
Dr. Crusher, please
report to Sick Bay.

513
00:25:41,250 --> 00:25:42,834
Is it Lieutenant Juarez?

514
00:25:42,875 --> 00:25:45,542
Yes, Doctor, her contractions
are now one minute apart.

515
00:25:45,583 --> 00:25:46,834
I'm on my way.

516
00:25:46,875 --> 00:25:48,208
Why don't you, uh...

517
00:25:48,250 --> 00:25:50,917
program up an artificial
dance partner?

518
00:25:50,959 --> 00:25:53,583
And don't be afraid
to experiment.

519
00:25:53,625 --> 00:25:54,583
I will.

520
00:25:54,625 --> 00:25:55,875
Thank you, Doctor.

521
00:25:55,917 --> 00:26:00,458
Computer, create dance partner--
female.

522
00:26:06,250 --> 00:26:07,917
Begin music.

523
00:26:07,959 --> 00:26:09,875
(<i> music starts</i> )

524
00:26:33,417 --> 00:26:36,667
RIKER:
Then just as the headsman swings
the axe and the blade is...

525
00:26:36,709 --> 00:26:38,583
<i>Commander Riker's</i>
<i>easygoing manner</i>

526
00:26:38,625 --> 00:26:40,875
<i>and sense of humor</i>
<i>is fascinating to me.</i>

527
00:26:40,917 --> 00:26:42,208
<i>I believe it to be one reason</i>

528
00:26:42,250 --> 00:26:44,500
<i>he is so popular</i>
<i>among the crew.</i>

529
00:26:44,542 --> 00:26:46,625
<i>It may also be</i>
<i>partly responsible</i>

530
00:26:46,667 --> 00:26:49,083
<i>for his success</i>
<i>in matters of love.</i>

531
00:26:49,125 --> 00:26:51,583
<i>There may be a correlation</i>
<i>between humor and sex.</i>

532
00:26:51,625 --> 00:26:55,166
<i>The need for more research</i>
<i>is clearly indicated.</i>

533
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:00,333
(<i> console beeping</i> )

534
00:27:00,375 --> 00:27:01,709
Commander.

535
00:27:04,625 --> 00:27:06,125
Picard to the Bridge.

536
00:27:06,166 --> 00:27:07,583
All stop.

537
00:27:07,625 --> 00:27:08,917
Aye, sir.

538
00:27:10,709 --> 00:27:14,083
DATA:
Sir, we have reached
the designated coordinates.

539
00:27:14,125 --> 00:27:15,667
Hold this position.

540
00:27:15,709 --> 00:27:17,458
Long range scan.

541
00:27:17,500 --> 00:27:19,750
Captain, I am
detecting a ship

542
00:27:19,792 --> 00:27:20,917
in the Neutral Zone.

543
00:27:20,959 --> 00:27:22,500
Configuration...

544
00:27:22,542 --> 00:27:25,458
Romulan warbird.

545
00:27:25,500 --> 00:27:27,750
Yellow Alert.

546
00:27:29,709 --> 00:27:32,125
Hail the warbird,
Mr. Worf.

547
00:27:32,166 --> 00:27:33,417
Aye, sir.

548
00:27:33,458 --> 00:27:35,458
They are responding.

549
00:27:35,500 --> 00:27:38,291
Text only.

550
00:27:38,333 --> 00:27:40,166
We are to proceed

551
00:27:40,208 --> 00:27:41,709
to the agreed
coordinates.

552
00:27:41,750 --> 00:27:48,500
Set course 037 mark 005,
warp four.

553
00:27:48,542 --> 00:27:50,917
Take us into the Neutral Zone,
Ensign.

554
00:27:58,125 --> 00:28:00,875
Captain, the warbird
is holding position.

555
00:28:00,917 --> 00:28:03,750
In three minutes, we will be
within phaser range.

556
00:28:03,792 --> 00:28:04,792
Red Alert.

557
00:28:04,834 --> 00:28:06,458
(<i> alarm blaring</i> )

558
00:28:07,709 --> 00:28:09,834
I trust my crew, Ambassador.

559
00:28:09,875 --> 00:28:11,917
They will take
no provocative action

560
00:28:11,959 --> 00:28:13,875
unless I order them.

561
00:28:15,959 --> 00:28:17,333
Hold position

562
00:28:17,375 --> 00:28:18,709
on these coordinates.

563
00:28:18,750 --> 00:28:20,333
Slow to half impulse.

564
00:28:20,375 --> 00:28:22,375
Open a channel.

565
00:28:23,709 --> 00:28:25,041
Open.

566
00:28:26,125 --> 00:28:28,917
I am Ambassador T'Pel.

567
00:28:28,959 --> 00:28:31,500
I am Admiral Mendak.

568
00:28:31,542 --> 00:28:33,083
There is no
established protocol

569
00:28:33,125 --> 00:28:35,208
for a meeting of this nature.

570
00:28:35,250 --> 00:28:37,375
The logical course
is that I transport

571
00:28:37,417 --> 00:28:39,834
aboard your ship and
begin the negotiations.

572
00:28:39,875 --> 00:28:41,250
Yes.

573
00:28:41,291 --> 00:28:45,208
Captain, I note
your defensive systems

574
00:28:45,250 --> 00:28:46,709
have been activated.

575
00:28:46,750 --> 00:28:48,041
As have yours.

576
00:28:48,083 --> 00:28:50,125
It was not meant
as an accusation.

577
00:28:50,166 --> 00:28:53,333
Indeed, I salute
your show of strength.

578
00:28:53,375 --> 00:28:56,667
Ambassador, we are honored
by your presence.

579
00:28:56,709 --> 00:28:59,917
You may transport aboard
at your convenience.

580
00:28:59,959 --> 00:29:01,625
The honor is mine.

581
00:29:03,500 --> 00:29:06,041
Have your transporter room
stand by.

582
00:29:06,083 --> 00:29:07,959
I will beam
aboard their ship

583
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,583
with no further delay.

584
00:29:09,625 --> 00:29:13,208
Ambassador, I urge you
once more to reconsider.

585
00:29:13,250 --> 00:29:16,208
The<i> Enterprise</i> can
accommodate a
Romulan delegation

586
00:29:16,250 --> 00:29:17,917
without sacrificing
our security or...

587
00:29:17,959 --> 00:29:21,291
Captain Picard, I find
your argument illogical.

588
00:29:21,333 --> 00:29:23,417
Please carry out
my instructions.

589
00:29:27,417 --> 00:29:28,709
Picard to Chief O'Brien.

590
00:29:28,750 --> 00:29:30,667
O'Brien here.

591
00:29:30,709 --> 00:29:33,583
Prepare to transport
Ambassador T'Pel to
the Romulan vessel.

592
00:29:33,625 --> 00:29:35,208
Aye, sir.

593
00:29:35,250 --> 00:29:37,667
Mr. Worf, maintain
a lock on her signal
once she's aboard.

594
00:29:37,709 --> 00:29:40,000
At the first sign of
trouble, I want to be
able to bring her back.

595
00:29:40,041 --> 00:29:41,709
Understood.

596
00:29:43,959 --> 00:29:45,834
Transporter activated.

597
00:29:45,875 --> 00:29:47,083
(<i> console beeping insistently)</i>

598
00:29:47,125 --> 00:29:48,208
Captain...

599
00:29:48,250 --> 00:29:49,250
O'BRIEN:
Transporter emergency!

600
00:29:49,291 --> 00:29:51,250
I'm losing her signal.

601
00:29:51,291 --> 00:29:53,083
Boosting power
to autosequencers.

602
00:29:53,125 --> 00:29:55,000
Engaging computer override.

603
00:29:55,041 --> 00:29:56,542
O'Brien, what happened
down there?

604
00:29:56,583 --> 00:29:58,250
I'm losing the pattern.

605
00:29:58,291 --> 00:30:00,583
Trying to reestablish.

606
00:30:02,333 --> 00:30:03,875
I'm sorry, sir.

607
00:30:03,917 --> 00:30:07,333
I wasn't able
to retrieve the signal.

608
00:30:07,375 --> 00:30:09,875
The Ambassador is dead.

609
00:30:14,959 --> 00:30:18,291
DATA:
<i>Second Officer's Personal Log,</i>
<i>supplemental.</i>

610
00:30:18,333 --> 00:30:21,291
<i>The risks aboard a starship</i>
<i>are accepted by all who serve</i>

611
00:30:21,333 --> 00:30:23,166
<i>but I have never failed</i>
<i>to observe</i>

612
00:30:23,208 --> 00:30:26,125
<i>a deep emotional response</i>
<i>to the loss of a comrade.</i>

613
00:30:26,166 --> 00:30:27,917
<i>It is at times like this</i>

614
00:30:27,959 --> 00:30:30,834
<i>that I greatly miss the ability</i>
<i>to share human feelings.</i>

615
00:30:30,875 --> 00:30:33,166
The signal lock
wasn't broken, sir.

616
00:30:33,208 --> 00:30:35,083
I had just entered
the transfer sequence

617
00:30:35,125 --> 00:30:37,583
when the Ambassador's
pattern began to break up.

618
00:30:37,625 --> 00:30:40,208
I tried to switch to
emergency manual control

619
00:30:40,250 --> 00:30:43,542
but the pattern
deteriorated too
quickly and...

620
00:30:43,583 --> 00:30:46,583
Captain, there is no prior
record of this type of accident

621
00:30:46,625 --> 00:30:48,500
occurring aboard a starship.

622
00:30:48,542 --> 00:30:49,959
Backup systems and safeguards

623
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,333
are designed to prevent
just such an occurrence.

624
00:30:52,375 --> 00:30:55,750
I can't find any system flaws
in the unit, Captain.

625
00:30:55,792 --> 00:30:57,375
The engineering status
reports were all normal

626
00:30:57,417 --> 00:30:58,875
none of the backups
were activated

627
00:30:58,917 --> 00:31:01,458
and the autosequencers were
all functioning normally.

628
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:04,500
Any prior malfunctions
on this transporter unit?
No, sir.

629
00:31:04,542 --> 00:31:06,959
In fact, we replaced
the transition coil
only last week.

630
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:08,166
Could there have been
some sort of

631
00:31:08,208 --> 00:31:09,417
interference
from the Romulans?

632
00:31:09,458 --> 00:31:10,667
Nothing that I could see.

633
00:31:10,709 --> 00:31:11,834
The shields were down.

634
00:31:11,875 --> 00:31:13,041
There was no power
interruption

635
00:31:13,083 --> 00:31:14,625
no subspace bias.

636
00:31:14,667 --> 00:31:16,750
I want this unit pulled
and its systems checked again

637
00:31:16,792 --> 00:31:20,041
and I want a level-one
diagnostic on all transporters.

638
00:31:20,083 --> 00:31:22,000
Yes, sir.

639
00:31:22,041 --> 00:31:23,333
Her molecular structure

640
00:31:23,375 --> 00:31:25,875
dissipated instantly
once the pattern was lost.

641
00:31:25,917 --> 00:31:28,291
There were some organic
compounds left on the pad

642
00:31:28,333 --> 00:31:30,709
but there wasn't enough
material to do an autopsy.

643
00:31:33,750 --> 00:31:35,792
To die...

644
00:31:37,583 --> 00:31:40,083
on a transporter.

645
00:31:40,125 --> 00:31:41,667
Hardly a fitting end

646
00:31:41,709 --> 00:31:44,166
for one of the Federation's
most honored diplomats.

647
00:31:44,208 --> 00:31:46,208
WORF:
Bridge to Captain Picard.

648
00:31:46,250 --> 00:31:47,709
Admiral Mendak is hailing.

649
00:31:47,750 --> 00:31:49,333
He wishes to speak with you.

650
00:31:51,083 --> 00:31:53,208
(<i> sighs</i> )

651
00:31:54,333 --> 00:31:56,625
We're still waiting, Captain.

652
00:31:56,667 --> 00:31:58,208
Is there a problem?

653
00:31:58,250 --> 00:31:59,917
PICARD:
There's been an accident.

654
00:31:59,959 --> 00:32:04,000
Ambassador T'Pel has been killed
in a transporter malfunction.

655
00:32:04,041 --> 00:32:06,625
What kind of malfunction?

656
00:32:06,667 --> 00:32:09,083
We are still investigating that.
As soon as...

657
00:32:09,125 --> 00:32:10,750
I should have known
the Federation

658
00:32:10,792 --> 00:32:12,875
wasn't serious
about this conference.

659
00:32:12,917 --> 00:32:14,417
Admiral, I assure you

660
00:32:14,458 --> 00:32:17,291
the Federation
places the highest priority

661
00:32:17,333 --> 00:32:19,291
on this mission and its goal.

662
00:32:19,333 --> 00:32:20,750
Well played, Captain.

663
00:32:20,792 --> 00:32:22,250
Well played.

664
00:32:22,291 --> 00:32:25,083
Starfleet opposes
normalization of relations

665
00:32:25,125 --> 00:32:26,583
with the Romulan Empire

666
00:32:26,625 --> 00:32:30,917
and so you are ordered
to create... an "accident."

667
00:32:30,959 --> 00:32:32,166
You are mistaken.

668
00:32:32,208 --> 00:32:33,834
I am ready and willing

669
00:32:33,875 --> 00:32:37,417
to discuss the establishment
of full diplomatic relations

670
00:32:37,458 --> 00:32:40,291
under the same terms
as Ambassador T'Pel.

671
00:32:40,333 --> 00:32:42,542
A generous offer, since you know

672
00:32:42,583 --> 00:32:45,792
that we were willing
to negotiate only with T'Pel.

673
00:32:45,834 --> 00:32:47,834
I salute you again, Captain.

674
00:32:47,875 --> 00:32:51,125
It was a maneuver
worthy of a Romulan.

675
00:32:51,166 --> 00:32:54,125
I suggest we both
leave the Neutral Zone

676
00:32:54,166 --> 00:32:58,125
before there
is another... "accident."

677
00:33:00,208 --> 00:33:02,083
Set course
for Federation territory.

678
00:33:02,125 --> 00:33:04,583
Warp two.

679
00:33:04,625 --> 00:33:06,250
Engage.

680
00:33:06,291 --> 00:33:09,375
Mr. Data, I want you to take
charge of this investigation.

681
00:33:09,417 --> 00:33:13,083
Study computer logs,
sensor information, everything.

682
00:33:13,125 --> 00:33:16,125
I refuse to believe that this
was a simple malfunction.

683
00:33:16,166 --> 00:33:17,625
Aye, sir.

684
00:33:19,500 --> 00:33:22,333
<i>Captain Picard was the person</i>
<i>who first interested me</i>

685
00:33:22,375 --> 00:33:24,250
<i>in the works</i>
<i>of Sir Arthur Conan Doyle.</i>

686
00:33:24,291 --> 00:33:27,041
<i>I have subsequently</i>
<i>become a great admirer</i>

687
00:33:27,083 --> 00:33:29,458
<i>of the fictional detective</i>
<i>Sherlock Holmes</i>

688
00:33:29,500 --> 00:33:31,417
<i>and his ability</i>
<i>to solve mysteries</i>

689
00:33:31,458 --> 00:33:34,750
<i>by careful examination</i>
<i>of the available evidence.</i>

690
00:33:43,542 --> 00:33:46,625
<i>I have found</i>
<i>Holmes' methodology</i>

691
00:33:46,667 --> 00:33:49,166
<i>of deductive reasoning</i>
<i>to be quite useful.</i>

692
00:33:49,208 --> 00:33:50,917
<i>One of his adages is</i>

693
00:33:50,959 --> 00:33:52,875
<i>that, once you have</i>
<i>eliminated the impossible</i>

694
00:33:52,917 --> 00:33:58,041
<i>whatever remains, however</i>
<i>improbable, must be the truth.</i>

695
00:33:59,792 --> 00:34:01,834
I'm sorry,
I don't have time

696
00:34:01,875 --> 00:34:03,834
to give you another lesson
right now, Data.

697
00:34:03,875 --> 00:34:05,375
That is not my purpose.

698
00:34:05,417 --> 00:34:08,166
I would like to examine
the remains of Ambassador T'Pel

699
00:34:08,208 --> 00:34:09,667
left on the transporter pad.

700
00:34:09,709 --> 00:34:12,417
I'm working on the report
right now.

701
00:34:12,458 --> 00:34:15,709
Have you
compared the genetic code

702
00:34:15,750 --> 00:34:19,583
with the Ambassador's last
recorded transporter ID traces?

703
00:34:19,625 --> 00:34:22,458
No, that's not
standard procedure. Why?

704
00:34:22,500 --> 00:34:26,375
I could be chasing an untamed
ornithoid without cause.

705
00:34:27,917 --> 00:34:29,959
A wild goose chase?

706
00:34:32,875 --> 00:34:34,542
All right.

707
00:34:34,583 --> 00:34:40,667
Computer, access the transporter
ID trace for Ambassador T'Pel.

708
00:34:41,959 --> 00:34:43,417
All right.

709
00:34:43,458 --> 00:34:45,834
There's the genetic record
of the Ambassador

710
00:34:45,875 --> 00:34:47,291
when she beamed aboard the
<i>Enterprise.</i>

711
00:34:47,333 --> 00:34:49,041
Now, the breakdown
of the organic material

712
00:34:49,083 --> 00:34:52,166
found on the transporter pad
should be identical.

713
00:34:54,041 --> 00:34:57,917
Mitochondrial structure
fits the general parameters.

714
00:34:57,959 --> 00:34:59,166
No change

715
00:34:59,208 --> 00:35:01,417
in the nucleotide bases.

716
00:35:01,458 --> 00:35:03,875
Hmm, there's
a slight discrepancy

717
00:35:03,917 --> 00:35:06,125
in the base pair sequence.

718
00:35:07,834 --> 00:35:10,709
Chemically, these
are identical, however

719
00:35:10,750 --> 00:35:12,667
the organic sample
from the transporter

720
00:35:12,709 --> 00:35:15,709
is showing numerous
single-bit errors--

721
00:35:15,750 --> 00:35:17,667
like replicated material.

722
00:35:17,709 --> 00:35:18,875
Can you postulate

723
00:35:18,917 --> 00:35:21,125
an explanation
for the discrepancy?

724
00:35:21,166 --> 00:35:24,875
I'd say the DNA was either
mutated by the transporter

725
00:35:24,917 --> 00:35:26,917
during the re-materialization
process...

726
00:35:26,959 --> 00:35:30,000
A supposition not supported
by the transporter records.

727
00:35:30,041 --> 00:35:34,834
...or these aren't the remains
of the Ambassador.

728
00:35:42,041 --> 00:35:44,250
The only abnormality
found during my investigation

729
00:35:44,291 --> 00:35:48,041
was a temporary increase in the
matter-to-energy signal ratio.

730
00:35:48,083 --> 00:35:49,208
Due to the circumstances

731
00:35:49,250 --> 00:35:50,917
I decided to investigate
the possibility

732
00:35:50,959 --> 00:35:54,375
that a<i> second</i> transporter signal
had caused the fluctuation.

733
00:35:54,417 --> 00:35:55,959
Although this is
highly improbable

734
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:57,709
it was the only
remaining theory.

735
00:35:57,750 --> 00:36:00,083
A second transporter signal--
from where?

736
00:36:00,125 --> 00:36:01,583
From the<i> Devoras.</i>

737
00:36:01,625 --> 00:36:02,959
Romulan transporters operate

738
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:05,166
on a similar subspace frequency
to our own.

739
00:36:05,208 --> 00:36:07,291
With only minor adjustments,
they can be made

740
00:36:07,333 --> 00:36:10,000
to simulate our own
transporter carrier wave.

741
00:36:10,041 --> 00:36:15,750
Are you saying they beamed
the Ambassador off our own pad?

742
00:36:15,792 --> 00:36:17,166
While simultaneously

743
00:36:17,208 --> 00:36:19,750
a small amount
of genetically similar material

744
00:36:19,792 --> 00:36:22,667
was left
in the Ambassador's place.

745
00:36:22,709 --> 00:36:24,333
To make us believe
that she had died

746
00:36:24,375 --> 00:36:25,834
as a result of the malfunction.

747
00:36:25,875 --> 00:36:27,291
Yes, sir.

748
00:36:27,333 --> 00:36:30,917
Mr. Worf,
where is the<i> Devoras</i> now?

749
00:36:30,959 --> 00:36:33,458
WORF:
The ship is still
in the Neutral Zone.

750
00:36:33,500 --> 00:36:38,709
On course 079 mark 125.
Speed: warp two.

751
00:36:38,750 --> 00:36:40,750
Heading for home.

752
00:36:40,792 --> 00:36:43,875
<i>The safest and most logical</i>
<i>decision in this situation</i>

753
00:36:43,917 --> 00:36:46,709
<i>is to contact Starfleet</i>
<i>and await further</i>
<i>instructions.</i>

754
00:36:46,750 --> 00:36:49,667
<i>However,</i>
<i>based on past experience</i>

755
00:36:49,709 --> 00:36:51,792
<i>I project only a 17% chance</i>

756
00:36:51,834 --> 00:36:54,500
<i>Captain Picard will choose</i>
<i>that alternative.</i>

757
00:36:55,917 --> 00:36:56,875
Red Alert.

758
00:36:56,917 --> 00:36:57,834
All hands

759
00:36:57,875 --> 00:36:59,959
stand to
battle stations.

760
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:01,959
(<i> alarm blaring</i> )

761
00:37:03,792 --> 00:37:05,959
Lay in an intercept course
to the Romulan ship.

762
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:08,500
Shields up.
Load all torpedo bays.
Stand by phasers.

763
00:37:08,542 --> 00:37:09,542
Warp factor eight.

764
00:37:09,583 --> 00:37:10,959
Engage.

765
00:37:12,917 --> 00:37:15,458
Open a channel to the<i> Devoras.</i>

766
00:37:15,500 --> 00:37:17,542
Aye, sir.

767
00:37:17,583 --> 00:37:19,166
No response.

768
00:37:19,208 --> 00:37:21,125
DATA:
The<i> Devoras</i> is dropping
out of warp, sir.

769
00:37:21,166 --> 00:37:22,834
Their weapon systems
are powering up.

770
00:37:22,875 --> 00:37:25,041
Go to impulse power.
Aye, sir.

771
00:37:32,125 --> 00:37:33,959
Message coming in, sir.

772
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:37,166
PICARD:
On screen.

773
00:37:37,208 --> 00:37:40,792
Captain, you agreed to leave
the Neutral Zone without...

774
00:37:40,834 --> 00:37:42,125
Admiral Mendak

775
00:37:42,166 --> 00:37:45,083
you have taken
our Ambassador captive.

776
00:37:45,125 --> 00:37:46,917
I can assure you

777
00:37:46,959 --> 00:37:50,834
there is no one being held
captive aboard this ship.

778
00:37:50,875 --> 00:37:55,083
We know about
the transporter "malfunction"

779
00:37:55,125 --> 00:37:57,375
and that you are holding
Ambassador T'Pel.

780
00:37:57,417 --> 00:37:58,709
WORF:
Captain

781
00:37:58,750 --> 00:38:01,583
Romulan warbird
de-cloaking to starboard.

782
00:38:08,041 --> 00:38:10,750
I suggest you leave...

783
00:38:10,792 --> 00:38:12,041
now.

784
00:38:12,083 --> 00:38:15,500
Admiral, it is my responsibility

785
00:38:15,542 --> 00:38:17,667
to protect the lives
of Federation citizens.

786
00:38:17,709 --> 00:38:20,417
I will not permit
this abduction to succeed.

787
00:38:20,458 --> 00:38:21,542
Captain, you're not going

788
00:38:21,583 --> 00:38:23,208
to start an incident
which might...

789
00:38:23,250 --> 00:38:25,750
Admiral Mendak, I will take
whatever action is necessary

790
00:38:25,792 --> 00:38:28,709
to obtain the return
of the Ambassador.

791
00:38:28,750 --> 00:38:31,917
<i>In the game of poker,</i>
<i>there is a moment</i>

792
00:38:31,959 --> 00:38:33,792
<i>when a player must decide</i>
<i>if an opponent</i>

793
00:38:33,834 --> 00:38:36,166
<i>is being deceptive or actually</i>
<i>holds a winning hand.</i>

794
00:38:36,208 --> 00:38:39,417
<i>This decision is based</i>
<i>not only on the odds</i>

795
00:38:39,458 --> 00:38:41,750
<i>but also on an appraisal</i>
<i>of the man--</i>

796
00:38:41,792 --> 00:38:44,375
<i>is he bluffing,</i>
<i>or does he have the cards?</i>

797
00:38:44,417 --> 00:38:46,917
MENDAK:
Fortunately, Captain

798
00:38:46,959 --> 00:38:49,083
I am not ready to start a war...

799
00:38:49,125 --> 00:38:51,166
today.

800
00:38:57,583 --> 00:38:59,041
T'Pel.

801
00:38:59,083 --> 00:39:02,125
Subcommander Selok, actually.

802
00:39:02,166 --> 00:39:03,959
A spy.

803
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:05,583
A patriot, Captain.

804
00:39:05,625 --> 00:39:09,041
She has performed her
service to the Empire

805
00:39:09,083 --> 00:39:10,458
with distinction.

806
00:39:10,500 --> 00:39:14,709
Thank you for your help,
Captain.

807
00:39:14,750 --> 00:39:18,291
MENDAK:
You see now that we are not
holding one of your citizens

808
00:39:18,333 --> 00:39:22,333
and we thank you for returning
our sister to us

809
00:39:22,375 --> 00:39:27,041
but my patience has limits.

810
00:39:27,083 --> 00:39:29,000
The game is over.

811
00:39:29,041 --> 00:39:31,834
I expect you to
leave peacefully...

812
00:39:31,875 --> 00:39:33,333
<i>now.</i>

813
00:39:34,625 --> 00:39:36,834
Captain, long-range sensors

814
00:39:36,875 --> 00:39:40,875
detect three Romulan warbirds
entering the sector.

815
00:39:40,917 --> 00:39:42,875
Some days you
get the bear

816
00:39:42,917 --> 00:39:45,709
and some days,
the bear gets you.

817
00:39:45,750 --> 00:39:47,792
Reverse course.

818
00:39:49,250 --> 00:39:51,208
Take us back into
Federation territory.

819
00:39:51,250 --> 00:39:52,208
Warp six.

820
00:39:52,250 --> 00:39:54,000
Engage.

821
00:40:06,125 --> 00:40:09,458
Keiko, I need your help.

822
00:40:09,500 --> 00:40:10,875
I have offended you

823
00:40:10,917 --> 00:40:13,083
and need to find a way
to rectify my mistake.

824
00:40:13,125 --> 00:40:14,792
I am not sure
what to do.

825
00:40:14,834 --> 00:40:16,875
You haven't offended me.

826
00:40:16,917 --> 00:40:18,667
I should not
have interfered.

827
00:40:18,709 --> 00:40:20,709
It would be best
if I apologize.

828
00:40:20,750 --> 00:40:22,959
It would be best
if you got dressed.

829
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:24,417
For the wedding.

830
00:40:24,458 --> 00:40:26,500
Oh.

831
00:40:26,542 --> 00:40:28,625
But...?

832
00:40:29,542 --> 00:40:31,125
Come here.

833
00:40:31,166 --> 00:40:33,458
I have the most
beautiful carnation

834
00:40:33,500 --> 00:40:36,041
for the father
of the bride.

835
00:40:36,083 --> 00:40:38,083
Now, don't be nervous.

836
00:40:38,125 --> 00:40:39,917
I am not nervous.

837
00:40:39,959 --> 00:40:41,875
I<i> am</i> confused.

838
00:40:41,917 --> 00:40:43,625
(<i> chuckles</i> )

839
00:40:48,500 --> 00:40:51,417
(<i> Japanese classical</i>
<i>court music plays</i> )

840
00:41:32,959 --> 00:41:34,500
(<i> music ends</i> )

841
00:41:34,542 --> 00:41:38,125
Since the days of the
first wooden sailing ships

842
00:41:38,166 --> 00:41:43,125
all Captains have enjoyed
the happy privilege

843
00:41:43,166 --> 00:41:47,041
of joining together two people

844
00:41:47,083 --> 00:41:50,750
in the bonds
of matrimony, and so...

845
00:41:50,792 --> 00:41:55,083
it is my honor to unite you,
Keiko Ishikawa

846
00:41:55,125 --> 00:42:00,208
and you, Miles Edward O'Brien,
together in matrimony...

847
00:42:00,250 --> 00:42:02,333
<i>There are still</i>
<i>many human emotions</i>

848
00:42:02,375 --> 00:42:06,834
<i>I do not fully comprehend--</i>
<i>anger, hatred, revenge--</i>

849
00:42:06,875 --> 00:42:10,375
<i>but I am not mystified</i>
<i>by the desire to be loved...</i>

850
00:42:10,417 --> 00:42:11,458
(<i> applause and cheers</i> )

851
00:42:11,500 --> 00:42:12,750
<i>...or the need for friendship.</i>

852
00:42:12,792 --> 00:42:16,959
<i>These are things</i>
<i>I do understand.</i>

853
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:19,083
(<i> applause continues</i> )

854
00:42:19,125 --> 00:42:21,208
Congratulations!

855
00:42:23,583 --> 00:42:25,667
(<i> dance music plays</i> )

856
00:42:43,917 --> 00:42:45,959
(<i> baby gurgling</i> )

857
00:42:52,291 --> 00:42:54,083
I was looking
for Dr. Crusher.

858
00:42:54,125 --> 00:42:55,458
Shh.

859
00:42:58,208 --> 00:43:00,083
DATA:
The Juarez child?

860
00:43:00,125 --> 00:43:02,625
PICARD:
Mm-hmm... a boy.

861
00:43:02,667 --> 00:43:06,000
At the same time we
were facing destruction

862
00:43:06,041 --> 00:43:09,458
this small miracle
was taking place.

863
00:43:13,458 --> 00:43:16,000
(<i> softly</i> ):
Welcome aboard.

864
00:43:21,500 --> 00:43:23,291
All systems normal, sir.

865
00:43:23,333 --> 00:43:25,917
We are on course
for Adelphous IV.

866
00:43:25,959 --> 00:43:28,583
Engineering is realigning
the main deflector dish

867
00:43:28,625 --> 00:43:30,834
Sick Bay reports
Lieutenant Umbato

868
00:43:30,875 --> 00:43:33,417
broke two ribs
during a holodeck exercise

869
00:43:33,458 --> 00:43:36,291
and sensors continue to gather
long-range information

870
00:43:36,333 --> 00:43:37,875
on the Murasaki quasar.

871
00:43:37,917 --> 00:43:38,875
Very well.

872
00:43:38,917 --> 00:43:39,917
I have the Bridge.

873
00:43:39,959 --> 00:43:41,750
Aye, sir.

874
00:43:41,792 --> 00:43:44,583
<i>If being human</i>
<i>is not simply a matter</i>

875
00:43:44,625 --> 00:43:46,667
<i>of being born flesh and blood</i>

876
00:43:46,709 --> 00:43:50,959
<i>if it is instead a way</i>
<i>of thinking, acting and</i>
<i>feeling</i>

877
00:43:51,000 --> 00:43:52,333
<i>then I am hopeful that one day</i>

878
00:43:52,375 --> 00:43:54,291
<i>I will discover</i>
<i>my own humanity.</i>

879
00:43:54,333 --> 00:43:56,125
Begin night watch.

880
00:43:56,166 --> 00:43:59,959
<i>Until then, Commander Maddox,</i>
<i>I will continue</i>

881
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:03,417
<i>learning, changing, growing</i>

882
00:44:03,458 --> 00:44:07,750
<i>and trying to become more</i>
<i>than what I am.</i>
